It's time to tear down our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done except a little decorating.
The ugly electric fireplace and the hearth must come out. We need to rebuild the chimney, replace the chipped plaster, and smooth it out. Then we'll build a custom-made wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the job is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dried out :(
Everything ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche has turned out well.
Here comes a new wardrobe in (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought of installing this nice little vent flap so that the chimney doesn't get damp.
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and the cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlay lies, I have made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Floor parts are ready and can be installed. We are currently having a tea break.
Buhu. Things are progressing slowly today because of the super complicated cuts around the doorposts, so that we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be reinstalled). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me.
Done, but at the end! The crowning moment was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. Tonight we'll sleep well!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator is coming in a month, so for now we have a raw plaster look.
A bit more DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel out the lower sections around the doorposts, where the floor is supposed to fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlay is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then out at 5 o'clock in the morning to pick up Item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap, and final push in the hallway, the skirtings are installed. The joints will be made once the adhesive is dry.
